<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T18:06:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-14T18:07:00-05:00" n="800" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                    <head>Polish Members of the House of Deputies</head>
                    <dateline>
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:53" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:53">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <p>The Polish members of the Chamber of Deputies of Prussia, at this moment
                        present in Berlin, join their German colleagues in expressing all the grief
                        and indignation they have experienced on learning of the abominable crime to
                        which the illustrious President Lincoln has fallen a victem, a martyr of the
                        great cause of the abolition of slavery.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>AUGUSTE MIEZKOWSKI.</item>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dr</hi>. LIBETT.</item>
                                <item>BOGUSTAVE LUBIENSKI.</item>
                                <item>LYZBOWSKI PILASKI.</item>
                                <item>THOBAVSKI.</item>
                                <item>ZYCHLINSKI.</item>
                                <item>DAMILEWSKI.</item>
                                <item>STANISLAU MOTLEY.</item>
                                <item>LEON WEGNER.</item>
                                <item>JOSEPH POTUTICKI.</item>
                                <item>KADIMIRZ CHIAPOWSKI.</item>
                                <item>F. RESPAZDEK.</item>
                                <item>JOSEPH BOLEWSKI.</item>
                                <item>CASIMIR KANTAK.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>